item.title: Kamala Harris' husband wants a strong Republican Party, Scaramucci calls him the 'best kind of alpha male'
item.description: The Trump campaign dismissed Doug's comment on the Republican party and said he is as irrelevant as a wet paper bag. Trump spokesperson Steven Cheung told Newsweek, "Nobody cares what Doug has to say. He's as irrelevant as a wet paper bag." Doug Emhoff in a podcast commented on the Republican Party and said US needs a stronger Republican Party.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'The worst is...': 'Living Nostradamus' warns of a potential US-China conflict
item.description: Brazilian psychic Athos Salomé warns of potential conflicts involving the US, China, Israel, and Iran. He highlights tensions in the South China Sea and the threat of cyberattacks as triggers for a US-China conflict. Salomé also predicts an Israel-Iran clash in 2024 linked to AI and EMP weapons. Chinese analyst Zheng Yongnian echoes concerns about rising Asian tensions.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Eco-activists throw soup on Van Gogh works in UK, hours after two jailed for same
item.description: Eco-activists threw soup on Vincent van Gogh artworks in the UK, just hours after a British judge sentenced two climate activists for a similar act in 2022. Phoebe Plummer and Anna Holland were convicted for throwing soup at Van Gogh's "Sunflowers" painting. They received prison sentences of two years and 20 months respectively.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Georgia governor says at least 11 people are dead in his state after Hurricane Helene
item.description: Hurricane Helene struck Florida's Big Bend area as a Category 4 storm with winds of 140 mph, causing severe flooding and power outages. Emergency crews are working to rescue trapped residents. The storm has resulted in multiple fatalities and extensive damage across several states, including North Carolina.

item.title: Nate Silver's latest poll forecast: 'You'd probably rather have Harris' hand to play'
item.description: In Nate Silver's recent election forecast update, Kamala Harris leads Donald Trump by three percentage points in national polls. His model suggests Harris has an advantage in key states like Pennsylvania, Michigan, and Wisconsin. Interestingly, Silver mentioned he would vote for Trump if Harris proposed banning poker, underscoring how personal interests can influence voting choices.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'She should be prosecuted': Trump on Nancy Pelosi and husband’s $500K visa stock trades
item.description: Donald Trump has called for Nancy Pelosi's prosecution, alleging her husband's stock trades ahead of a DOJ lawsuit against Visa raise ethical concerns. He accused Pelosi of having inside knowledge and tipping off her husband before he sold shares in Visa. A representative for Pelosi denied any wrongdoing.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Kimberly Guilfoyle floating anti-Kamala story for 25 years. The truth is...'
item.description: ​"So what if Kamala voiced her fierce opposition all those years ago? If the story is true -- if Kamala did discourage Terence Hallinan from hiring Kimberly–maybe Kamala was just prescient. Maybe Kamala could see back then what it took me 20 years to learn. Kimberly doesn’t believe in anything but Kimberly," Jami wrote explaining that this job-snub story comes back again and again whenever Kimberly needs limelight and relevance.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Florida man kayaking in his living room during Hurricane Helene, video viral
item.description: Matt Heller of Tampa, Florida, used a kayak to navigate his flooded living room as Hurricane Helene's storm surge rapidly rose to 4 feet. Documented on TikTok, the event highlighted record-breaking surges in Tampa Bay, reaching up to 7 feet in some areas. The hurricane caused extensive damage and left millions without power.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Princess Diana was heartbroken over gossip on Prince Harry's 'biological father'
item.description: Princess Diana felt heartbroken over rumors claiming her riding instructor James Hewitt as Prince Harry's father. Her hairdresser Richard Dalton clarified that Harry was born before Diana met Hewitt and said that the red hair trait Harry got from the Spencer family. Dalton’s memoir unveils unknown aspects of Diana’s life and her relationship with Hewitt.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Was it Olivia Nuzzi? Was it Kennedy Jr? Conflicting reports on who made first move
item.description: Multiple sources revealed to Vanity Fair that Nuzzi and Kennedy went on a hike during the interview in November, last year. Kennedy was an Independent presidential candidate then. He allegedly grabbed Nuzzi's hand. Nuzzi told this to a colleague who too claimed to have a "creepy" encounter with Kennedy Jr before.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Jesus f**k': Prince Harry at Jimmy Fallon's spooky show; fans say 'the man is American now'
item.description: Harry's appearance won the hearts of social media users though he was called "potty-mothed", "foul-mouthed" in some news reports. Appearing on Jimmy Fallon show for this fun certified him as an American, an X post said in praise of Harry. "Prince Harry on Jimmy Fallon enjoying some spooky fun. LMAO, that man is American now," it said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Hurricane Helene hits Florida: Residents displaced, streets flooded
Over 30,000 crossed into Syria from Lebanon in past days, says UN
item.description: Over the past 72 hours, more than 30,000 individuals, primarily Syrians, have crossed into Syria from Lebanon due to an intensifying conflict between Israeli forces and Hezbollah. The UN refugee agency indicates that approximately half of these refugees are children and adolescents. Women are making the crossing in greater numbers compared to men.

item.title: Landslide in western Indonesia gold mine kills 15, dozens missing
item.description: A deadly landslide at a gold mine in Western Sumatra, Indonesia, has claimed at least 15 lives and left dozens missing following heavy rainfall. Rescue efforts are ongoing but hindered by the site's remote location. The legality of the mining operation is still undetermined. Unlicensed mines are prevalent in the area.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Watch: Saturn emerges from behind the Moon in rare video
item.description: Astrophotographer Andrew McCarthy captured a dramatic video of Saturn emerging from behind the Moon and shared it on social media. Enhanced with an infrared filter for better visibility, the footage shows Saturn's rings as it reappears from the Moon’s shadow. This phenomenon, known as occultation, has intrigued many astronomy enthusiasts and social media users.
item.dc:creator: TOI Science Desk

item.title: Hurricane Helene weakens to a Category 1 storm
item.description: Hurricane Helene has downgraded to a Category 1 storm with maximum sustained winds of 75 mph. Initially striking Florida as a Category 4 hurricane, it caused severe flooding and power outages affecting over 885,000 homes and businesses. Now moving northward to Georgia, the storm continues to impact thousands of residents.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Earth to get second moon from September 29 to November 25: How to watch
item.description: Earth is set to gain a temporary mini-moon this autumn with the arrival of asteroid 2024 PT5. The asteroid, measuring about 33 feet wide, will orbit Earth from September 29 to November 25 before leaving its gravitational pull. Professional telescopes will capture images of this rare occurrence, emphasizing the dynamic activity in our solar system.
item.dc:creator: TOI Science Desk

item.title: Justice or torture: Alabama execute Alan Eugene Miller by Nitrogen hypoxia
item.description: Alan Eugene Miller was executed in Alabama by nitrogen hypoxia for the 1999 murders of three men. He became the second inmate to die by this method. The execution, which lasted about 15 minutes, was described as going according to plan. This method has been criticized as potentially causing severe suffering.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Watch: Haitian President's UN speech goes viral after water pitcher mishap
item.description: During his UN speech, Haitian President Edgard Leblanc Fils became an internet sensation after spilling water on himself. The incident sparked viral memes but did not overshadow his call for global support to combat gang violence and human rights violations in Haiti. He also demanded reparations for historical injustices and addressed Donald Trump's controversial remarks about Haitian immigrants.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Plans underway for bronze sculpture honouring former Victorian premier Daniel Andrews
item.description: A bronze sculpture is being planned to honour former Victorian premier Daniel Andrews for his over 3000 days in office. This initiative follows a policy from the 1990s aimed at recognising long-serving premiers. The Victorian government has confirmed that planning is underway, with the Department of Premier and Cabinet initiating this process.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
